<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-31T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="295" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d295">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1514.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-31T15:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1915—3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 12, 9 a.m., Department’s March 18, 5 p.m., reference credit
                            order 1334. In Department’s opinion authorization by Dominican Congress
                            necessary. Department therefore disapproved credit order 1334.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
